  "text_preview": "\"raised\" American Sign Language (ASL) ASL University ► American Sign Language: \"raised\" or \"grow up\" / \"grew up\" The sign for \"raised\" or \"grew-up\" shows the height of a person as they grow up. Put your hand out in front of you, palm down. Lift the hand upward in a smooth steady motion. RAISED / grow up: GROW-UP (animated gif) Notes: If you want to say that you like to raise \"plants\" you would instead sign \" take care of .\" If you are talking about a fund raiser - there are several ways to sign it but a fairly safe way would be to sign \" MONEY , EARN\" or even \"MONEY COLLECT.\" Also see: GROW Also see: \" Context-based Conjugation: GROW-UP/RAISED \" Want to help support ASL University? It's easy : DONATE ( Thanks! ) (You don't need a PayPal account. Just look for the credit card logos and clic"
}
